What you need to know:

Whiteflies suck the cell sap from plant leaves and produce a sticky substance known as honeydew.The presence of eggs on the leaves is an indication of a new generation of whiteflies, hence the need to control them.Yellow sticky traps can also be used to control the whiteflies as the pest are attracted to the yellow colour.Thrips are attracted to white and yellow blossoms and easily transmit the tomato spotted wilt virus.